00:39:42.530 --> 00:39:44.460
NOT ONLY
ON FIRM GROUND

00:39:44.460 --> 00:39:46.660
THE RUBBISH AND
DAMAGE ACCUMULATES;

00:39:46.660 --> 00:39:49.500
THE SEA ALSO HAS
HAD HER SHARE.

00:39:49.500 --> 00:39:52.160
THE SEA BED WAS ALWAYS
GENEROUS TO MANKIND,

00:39:52.160 --> 00:39:54.360
WHO IN TURN GENERALLY
RESPONDED WITH SINCERE

00:39:54.360 --> 00:39:57.160
GRATITUDE - UNTIL
THE 20TH CENTURY,

00:39:57.160 --> 00:39:59.200
THAT IS, WHEN
INDUSTRIAL FISHING

00:39:59.200 --> 00:40:01.530
MADE ITS APPEARANCE
ON THE GLOBAL SCENE.

00:40:01.530 --> 00:40:03.660
FROM THAT MOMENT ON,
OVER EXPLOITATION

00:40:03.660 --> 00:40:05.260
HAS BEEN THE NORM.

00:40:05.260 --> 00:40:07.530
AND NOW OVER HALF OF ALL
COMMERCIAL FISH SPECIES

00:40:07.530 --> 00:40:09.160
ARE IN DANGER
OF EXTINCTION.

00:40:09.160 --> 00:40:11.100
JUST A QUARTER OF ALL
THE SEA'S RESOURCES

00:40:11.100 --> 00:40:14.000
ARE SAFE FROM THIS
TYPE OF DEVASTATION.

00:40:14.000 --> 00:40:16.900
NATURAL DISASTERS CAUSED
BY CHEMICAL PRODUCTS

00:40:16.900 --> 00:40:20.460
HAVE INCREASED
SINCE 1960.

00:40:20.460 --> 00:40:26.300
ONE OF THE GREATEST
SOURCES IS DUMPING.

00:40:26.300 --> 00:40:30.360
BETWEEN ONE ONE-THOUSANDTH
AND TWO THOUSANDTHS OF THE

00:40:30.360 --> 00:40:33.560
WORLD'S OIL PRODUCTION
ENDS UP IN THE SEA.

00:40:33.560 --> 00:40:35.930
SHIPPING ACCIDENTS,
PETROL STATIONS,

00:40:35.930 --> 00:40:37.830
AND REFINERIES DUMP
ALMOST THREE MILLION

00:40:37.830 --> 00:40:40.100
TONS OF OIL INTO
THE WATER EACH YEAR

00:40:40.100 --> 00:40:49.800
CAUSING IRREVERSIBLE
DAMAGE TO THE ENVIRONMENT.

00:40:49.800 --> 00:40:53.460
THE TRANSFORMATION OF
TROPICAL RAIN FORESTS

00:40:53.460 --> 00:40:56.060
INTO CULTIVATED FIELDS,

00:40:56.060 --> 00:40:58.130
OF RIVER BANKS
INTO CAR PARKS,

00:40:58.130 --> 00:40:59.830
OR SEA BEDS
INTO DESERTS,

00:40:59.830 --> 00:41:02.560
OBVIOUSLY HAVE SERIOUS
CONSEQUENCES FOR ALL OF US

00:41:02.560 --> 00:41:04.230
- NOT ONLY FOR
THOSE COMMUNITIES

00:41:04.230 --> 00:41:10.000
THAT SUFFER
MOST DIRECTLY.

00:41:10.000 --> 00:41:12.930
IT IS CALCULATED THAT
HUMAN BEINGS HAVE

00:41:12.930 --> 00:41:16.030
INCREASED THE RATE OF
ANIMAL SPECIES EXTINCTION

00:41:16.030 --> 00:41:20.560
BY UP TO 100,000%
OF ITS NATURAL PACE.

00:41:40.800 --> 00:41:43.500
WE HAVE DESTROYED, OR
ARE IN THE PROCESS OF

00:41:43.500 --> 00:41:46.960
DESTROYING, 12% OF ALL
BIRDS, 25% OF MAMMALS,

00:41:46.960 --> 00:41:50.300
AND 32% OF
ALL AMPHIBIANS.

00:41:50.300 --> 00:41:53.000
IF WE DON'T
STOP THIS PROCESS

00:41:53.000 --> 00:41:55.530
AND ACHIEVE
SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT

00:41:55.530 --> 00:42:00.830
WE WILL SOON LOSE CONTROL
OVER OUR OWN SURVIVAL.

00:42:14.260 --> 00:42:17.030
THERE'S NO CONSENSUS
ON THE CAUSES OF

00:42:17.030 --> 00:42:19.860
THE EARTH'S RECENT
CLIMATIC CHANGES.

00:42:19.860 --> 00:42:21.800
IT'S CERTAINLY TRUE THAT
THE GREENHOUSE EFFECT

00:42:21.800 --> 00:42:23.860
ISN'T THE RESULT
EXCLUSIVELY

00:42:23.860 --> 00:42:25.630
OF HUMAN ACTIVITY.

00:42:25.630 --> 00:42:28.730
IN FACT, WITHOUT IT THE
AVERAGE TEMPERATURE

00:42:28.730 --> 00:42:34.030
OF THE EARTH WOULD BE
18 DEGREES BELOW ZERO.

00:42:34.030 --> 00:42:37.560
OUR ATMOSPHERE NEEDS
CARBON DIOXIDE, CO2,

00:42:37.560 --> 00:42:40.230
TO REGULATE GLOBAL
TEMPERATURE.

00:42:40.230 --> 00:42:42.460
HOWEVER, THERE<i> IS</i>
SCIENTIFIC CONSENSUS

00:42:42.460 --> 00:42:44.530
REGARDING THE ARTIFICIAL
INCREASES IN CERTAIN

00:42:44.530 --> 00:42:47.000
FACTORS THAT CAUSE
TEMPERATURE INCREASES

00:42:47.000 --> 00:42:50.400
AND DISORDERS IN
NATURAL WEATHER CYCLES.

00:43:04.030 --> 00:43:06.830
AND THIS IS EXACTLY
WHAT IS HAPPENING.

00:43:06.830 --> 00:43:09.300
GLOBAL CLIMATE IS BEING
ALTERED AS A CONSEQUENCE

00:43:09.300 --> 00:43:11.400
OF THE INCREASED
CONCENTRATION

00:43:11.400 --> 00:43:12.800
OF GREENHOUSE GASES.

00:43:12.800 --> 00:43:15.130
THESE GASES WILL INCREASE
THE PLANET'S TEMPERATURE

00:43:15.130 --> 00:43:19.330
BETWEEN 1.5 AND 4.5
DEGREES CELSIUS.

00:43:19.330 --> 00:43:22.000
THE CONSEQUENCES
CAN ALREADY BE SEEN:

00:43:22.000 --> 00:43:26.530
FLOODING OF COASTAL AREAS
AND CITIES, FIERCER STORMS,

00:43:26.530 --> 00:43:28.960
THE EXTINCTION OF
COUNTLESS ANIMAL

00:43:28.960 --> 00:43:32.430
AND PLANT SPECIES,
MORE DROUGHTS.

00:44:08.160 --> 00:44:11.330
MANKIND'S ENERGY USE HAS
BEEN 16 TIMES GREATER

00:44:11.330 --> 00:44:14.930
IN THE 20TH CENTURY THAN
BEFORE, AND 80% OF THIS

00:44:14.930 --> 00:44:18.230
ENERGY HAS BEEN OBTAINED
FROM FOSSIL FUEL, COAL AND

00:44:18.230 --> 00:44:20.900
PETROLEUM PRODUCTS WHICH
HAS BEEN RESPONSIBLE FOR

00:44:20.900 --> 00:44:23.900
A 25% INCREASE OF CO2
IN THE ATMOSPHERE

00:44:23.900 --> 00:44:27.330
OVER THE LAST CENTURY.

00:44:36.000 --> 00:44:39.000
WE ARE CREATING A WORLD
THAT IS BASED ON

00:44:39.000 --> 00:44:42.500
BIG CITIES, A WORLD OF
CONCRETE AND CEMENT.

00:44:42.500 --> 00:44:45.900
CITIES CONTAMINATED BY
SMOKE, DESIGNED FOR HUSTLE

00:44:45.900 --> 00:44:49.900
AND BUSTLE, FOR THE WASTE
OF RESOURCES AND ENERGY.

00:44:49.900 --> 00:44:51.800
WE HAVE CREATED
AN URBAN WORLD

00:44:51.800 --> 00:44:54.030
WITH AN UNSUSTAINABLE
PRODUCTION SYSTEM

00:44:54.030 --> 00:44:57.330
AND LEVELS OF CONSUMPTION,
AND IT IS UNSUSTAINABLE

00:44:57.330 --> 00:44:59.630
BECAUSE OF TWO
BASIC PRINCIPLES.

00:44:59.630 --> 00:45:01.730
IT'S BASED ON THE
INDISCRIMINATE USE OF

00:45:01.730 --> 00:45:03.960
SOURCE MATERIALS AND
IS CONCEIVED IN A WAY

00:45:03.960 --> 00:45:05.700
THAT TWO-THIRDS OF
THE HUMAN RACE

00:45:05.700 --> 00:45:10.130
CAN NEVER ACCESS
THE PROFITS.

00:45:54.400 --> 00:45:57.430
IF WE CONSIDER THE FACT
THAT FIRST WORLD COUNTRIES

00:45:57.430 --> 00:46:00.200
CONSUME 90% OF THE
DIRTY ENERGY PRODUCED

00:46:00.200 --> 00:46:02.260
AND THAT THIRD
WORLD COUNTRIES

00:46:02.260 --> 00:46:04.260
SUFFER THE WORST
CONSEQUENCES OF THE

00:46:04.260 --> 00:46:06.900
NATURAL DISASTERS
CAUSED BY CLIMATE CHANGE,

00:46:06.900 --> 00:46:09.260
WE FIND OURSELVES
BACK AT SQUARE ONE.

00:46:09.260 --> 00:46:11.330
IS THE ENVIRONMENTAL
DAMAGE SUFFERED

00:46:11.330 --> 00:46:15.130
THE SAME WAY IN MALI
AS IN CHICAGO?

00:46:15.130 --> 00:46:19.960
OBVIOUSLY, IT'S NOT.

00:46:37.700 --> 00:46:40.530
ONE OF THE TANGIBLE
CONSEQUENCES OF CLIMATE

00:46:40.530 --> 00:46:44.330
CHANGE IS THE DIZZYING
ADVANCE OF THE DESERT.

00:46:44.330 --> 00:46:47.300
THIS OASIS ONCE STRETCHED
OVER TWICE THE AREA

00:46:47.300 --> 00:46:49.830
IT DOES NOW AND THAT WAS
JUST A FEW YEARS AGO.

00:46:49.830 --> 00:46:54.560
NOT LONG FROM NOW IT
PROBABLY WON'T EVEN EXIST.

00:46:54.560 --> 00:46:57.900
IN THE DESERT AND
SURROUNDING AREAS

00:46:57.900 --> 00:47:00.760
THERE HAVE ALWAYS BEEN
DROUGHTS AND FAMINE

00:47:00.760 --> 00:47:07.060
BUT THEY WERE OCCASIONAL
AND PREDICTABLE.

00:47:07.060 --> 00:47:11.960
OVER THE PAST 30 YEARS THE
SLOW BUT UNSTOPPABLE RISE

00:47:11.960 --> 00:47:14.730
IN GLOBAL TEMPERATURES
HAS DRIED UP WELLS

00:47:14.730 --> 00:47:17.130
AND DEVASTATED
GRAZING AREAS

00:47:17.130 --> 00:47:20.800
ON THE FRINGES
OF OUR DESERTS.

00:47:29.600 --> 00:47:32.930
NOMADIC PEOPLES HAVE
HAD TO ABANDON THEIR

00:47:32.930 --> 00:47:35.860
TRADITIONAL WAYS OF LIFE
AND MOVE TO CITIES LIKE

00:47:35.860 --> 00:47:42.860
BAMAKO OR NIENA.

00:47:42.860 --> 00:47:45.300
THERE MIGHT BE OTHER
CAUSES TO TAKE INTO

00:47:45.300 --> 00:47:47.960
ACCOUNT BUT HARDLY ANYONE
NOW DOUBTS THAT OUR MODEL

00:47:47.960 --> 00:47:50.230
OF DEVELOPMENT HAS AIDED
IN THE INCREASED RATE OF

00:47:50.230 --> 00:47:53.760
FLOODS AND DROUGHTS OVER
THE LAST FEW DECADES.

00:48:09.300 --> 00:48:12.830
IN INDONESIA, TREMENDOUS
SPATES OF RAINFALL

00:48:12.830 --> 00:48:15.100
HAVE ADDED TO
DEFORESTATION AND

00:48:15.100 --> 00:48:18.100
CAUSED SIGNIFICANT
LOSS OF LAND.

00:48:18.100 --> 00:48:20.400
MANY INHABITANTS
OF BORNEO AND SUMATRA

00:48:20.400 --> 00:48:22.800
HAVE LEFT THE JUNGLE TO
CROWD TOGETHER IN CITIES

00:48:22.800 --> 00:48:25.100
SUCH AS JOYAKARTA WHERE
THEY FESTER WITHOUT

00:48:25.100 --> 00:48:29.100
HARDLY EVEN THE MOST
BASIC OF SERVICES.

00:48:40.800 --> 00:48:44.130
IT'S A REALITY WE CANNOT
JUST CLOSE OUR EYES TO,

00:48:44.130 --> 00:48:47.760
FROM WHICH WE CAN
SIMPLY WALK AWAY.

00:48:47.760 --> 00:48:50.230
THE POOR SUFFER THE
CONSEQUENCES MANIFEST

00:48:50.230 --> 00:48:52.800
IN A NATURAL SYSTEM
SO PROFITS MAY BE

00:48:52.800 --> 00:48:56.630
ACCUMULATED IN FIRST
WORLD COUNTRIES.

00:48:56.630 --> 00:48:58.760
THE LARGE SCALE
DEFORESTATION PROJECTS

00:48:58.760 --> 00:49:01.330
OCCURRING IN PLACES SUCH
AS THE AMAZON OR INDONESIA

00:49:01.330 --> 00:49:03.760
START IN SOME SENSES
WITH THE DEMAND FOR

00:49:03.760 --> 00:49:06.360
MEAT OR PAPER
IN OTHER PLACES

00:49:06.360 --> 00:49:08.060
FAR REMOVED FROM
THOSE FORESTS.

00:49:08.060 --> 00:49:10.200
THE NEGATIVE IMPACT
OF CLIMATE CHANGE

00:49:10.200 --> 00:49:12.400
IS DISPROPORTIONATELY
AFFECTING THE RICH

00:49:12.400 --> 00:49:18.230
AND THE POOR,
BUT NOT ALIKE.

00:49:18.230 --> 00:49:21.400
AND WE'D BE DECEIVING
OURSELVES IF WE THOUGHT

00:49:21.400 --> 00:49:24.130
THAT BY SIMPLY MOVING
THE RISKS OUT OF OUR OWN

00:49:24.130 --> 00:49:26.260
BACK YARDS AND
INTO SOMEBODY ELSE'S

00:49:26.260 --> 00:49:28.500
WE COULD BE FREE
OF THE CONSEQUENCES.

00:49:28.500 --> 00:49:31.160
IN A GLOBALIZED WORLD,
DAMAGE TO THE ENVIRONMENT

00:49:31.160 --> 00:49:32.660
IS ALSO GLOBAL.

00:49:32.660 --> 00:49:34.660
THE CURRENT PRODUCTION
AND DEVELOPMENT SYSTEM

00:49:34.660 --> 00:49:37.760
IS SIMPLY UNVIABLE OVER
THE MIDDLE AND LONG TERM.

00:49:37.760 --> 00:49:40.560
CURRENT TECHNOLOGY COULD
ALLOW US TO PRODUCE AND

00:49:40.560 --> 00:49:43.600
CONSUME IN A SUSTAINABLE
WAY BY CALCULATING RISKS

00:49:43.600 --> 00:49:46.830
AND AVOIDING TURNING 80%
OF MANKIND'S PRODUCTION

00:49:46.830 --> 00:49:51.130
INTO A WASTE DUMP FOR
THE REST OF THE WORLD.

00:51:04.060 --> 00:51:06.660
APPLYING THE MODEL,
HOWEVER, CHANGING PEOPLES'

00:51:06.660 --> 00:51:09.900
HABITS ISN'T SIMPLY AN
OPTION, IT'S A NECESSITY.

00:51:09.900 --> 00:51:12.130
AND THE SOONER WE START
THE SMALLER THE PRICE

00:51:12.130 --> 00:51:14.200
THAT FUTURE GENERATIONS
WILL HAVE TO PAY

00:51:14.200 --> 00:51:18.700
FOR OUR LACK OF
RESPONSIBILITY.